  <p>Factual and grammatical errors, including errors in world knowledge, errors within the article, overly bold claims, overgeneralization, statistical and numerical errors, and spelling and grammar.</p>
  {% endcall %}
  {% call accordion("rev-01-b", "Brevity — what does this filter target?") %}
  <p>Unnecessary words: using multiple vague words where fewer will do, repeated words, and redundant words.</p>
  {% endcall %}
  {% call accordion("rev-01-c", "Clarity — what does this filter target?") %}
  <p>Vague or ambiguous language: vague expressions, lexical ambiguity, referential ambiguity, syntactic ambiguity, and garden-path sentences.</p>
  {% endcall %}
  {% call accordion("rev-01-d", "Objectivity — what does this filter target?") %}
  <p>Subjective language: focusing on people and feelings rather than things and ideas, emotive wording, and excessive personalization.</p>
  {% endcall %}
  {% call accordion("rev-01-e", "Formality — what does this filter target?") %}
  <p>Informal language: contractions with apostrophes, undefined abbreviations, slang, informal terms, and rhetorical questions.</p>
